'''Wundanyi''' is a town in the [[Taita-Taveta County]] of [[Kenya]]. Other urban centres in the county include [[Voi]], [[Taveta, Kenya|Taveta]] and [[Mwatate]].<ref>{{cite web| url=http://taitataveta.go.ke/about_government| title=Taita-Taveta County Profile |accessdate=14 September 2016 | date=14 September 2016 |publisher=[[Taita-Taveta County|Taita-Taveta County Government]] |location=Mwatate | author=Taita-Taveta County}}</ref>
==Location== Wundanyi is located approximately {{convert|17|km|0}} north of [[Mwatate]], the location of the county headquarters.<ref>{{cite web|last=Globefeed,com| url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Kenya_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Mwatate%2C%20Taita-Taveta%20County%2C%20Kenya&toplace=Wundanyi%2C%20Taita-Taveta%20County%2C%20Kenya%2C&dt1=ChIJ3ZmgJpTeOBgRwQm01Gdjw5M&dt2=ChIJARGoEHYhORgRrZh-bpNk_24 | title=Distance between Mwatate, Taita-Taveta County, Kenya and Wundanyi, Taita-Taveta County, Kenya |accessdate=14 September 2016 | date=14 September 2016 |publisher=Globefeed.com}}</ref> This is about {{convert|40|km|0}} west of Voi, the largest town in the county.<ref>{{cite web| url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Kenya_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Voi%2C%20Taita-Taveta%20County%2C%20Kenya&toplace=Wundanyi%2C%20Taita-Taveta%20County%2C%20Kenya%2C&dt1=ChIJwUgHhFUpORgRaUxHbrd5KGE&dt2=ChIJARGoEHYhORgRrZh-bpNk_24 | title= Distance between Voi, Taita-Taveta County, Kenya and Wundanyi, Taita-Taveta County, Kenya | accessdate=14 September 2016 | date=14 September 2016 | publisher=Globefeed.com| author=Globefeed.com}}</ref> Wundanyi is about {{convert|195|km|0}} north-west of the port of [[Mombasa]], the nearest large city.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=14 September 2016 | url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Kenya_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Mombasa%2C%20Mombasa%20County%2C%20Kenya&toplace=Wundanyi%2C%20Taita-Taveta%20County%2C%20Kenya%2C&dt1=ChIJfSzAjucSQBgRWtvQNbyLYcs&dt2=ChIJARGoEHYhORgRrZh-bpNk_24 | date=14 September 2016 |title= Distance between Mombasa, Mombasa County, Kenya and Wundanyi, Taita-Taveta County, Kenya | publisher=Globefeed.com | author=Globefeed.com}}</ref> This is about {{convert|368|km|0}} south-east of [[Nairobi]], the capital and largest city of Kenya.<ref>{{cite web|accessdate=14 September 2016 | author=Globefeed.com| url=http://distancecalculator.globefeed.com/Kenya_Distance_Result.asp?fromplace=Nairobi%2C%20Nairobi%20County%2C%20Kenya&toplace=Wundanyi%2C%20Taita-Taveta%20County%2C%20Kenya%2C&dt1=ChIJp0lN2HIRLxgRTJKXslQCz_c&dt2=ChIJARGoEHYhORgRrZh-bpNk_24 |publisher=Globefeed.com | date=14 September 2016 | title= Distance between Nairobi, Nairobi County, Kenya and Wundanyi, Taita-Taveta County, Kenya}}</ref> The coordinates of Wundanyi are 03°23'54.0"S. 38°21'37.9"E (Latitude:-3.398329; Longitude:38.360526).<ref>{{google maps| url=https://www.google.com/maps/place/3%C2%B023'54.0%22S+38%C2%B021'37.9%22E/@-3.3983236,38.3583427,449m/data=!3m2!1e3!4b1!4m5!3m4!1s0x0:0x0!8m2!3d-3.398329!4d38.360526|title=Location of Wundanyi, Taita-Taveta County, Kenya| accessdate=14 September 2016}}</ref>
==Overview== The town is a popular base for [[hiking]], while local attractions include the [[Ngangao Forest]], known for its [[butterfly|butterflies]], ''Wesu Rock'' and the ''Cave of Skulls''.<ref name="Parkinson" /> Shomoto Hill, across the valley from Wundanyi was the formal place of execution for the [[Taita people|Taita]].<ref>{{cite book|author=Trillo, Richard|date=2010| title=The Rough Guide to Kenya| location=London|publisher=Penguin| page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=B6dEW14KykIC&pg=PA332 332]|isbn=978-1-84836-137-9}}</ref> Wundanyi is the centre of an [[agricultural]] area and the surrounding slopes are highly [[terrace (agriculture)|terraced]].<ref name="Parkinson">{{cite book| author1=Parkinson, Tom |author2=Phillips, Matt |author3=Gourlay, Will |lastauthoramp=yes |date=2006| title=Kenya|series=Lonely Planet Country Guide|page=[https://books.google.com/books?id=TTf0Aki6AUQC&pg=PA149 149]|isbn=978-1-74059-743-2}}</ref>
==Population== In 2011, the population of Taita-Taveta County was quoted at 284,657.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nation.co.ke/counties/Taita-Taveta-at-a-glance-/1107872-1165320-b5ngfdz/index.html | title= Taita Taveta at a glance| date=18 May 2011 | accessdate=14 September 2016 | newspaper=[[Daily Nation]] | location=Nairobi |last=Daily Nation}}</ref> As of May 2015, the population of Wundayi town was estimated at 21.9 percent of the county population,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:06uj-fO1Xf0J:https://www.humanitarianresponse.info/es/system/files/documents/files/taita-taveta_sdr_may_2015.docx+&cd=6&hl=en&ct=clnk&gl=us | title=Taita-Taveta County: Secondary Data Review |accessdate=14 September 2016 | date= 31 May 2015 | publisher=HumanitarianResponse.Info (HRI) | last=HRI}}</ref> about 62,340 people.
